<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 of 16 March 1987 on the common organization of the market in wine (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2087/97 (2), and in particular Articles 32 (5) and 83 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 16. m&auml;rtsi 1987. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 veinituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2087/97, eriti selle artikli 32 l&otilde;iget 5 ja artiklit 83, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the forward estimate drawn up for the 1997/98 wine year indicates that the quantities of table wine available at the beginning of the wine year exceed by more than four months' supply those normally used up over the year; whereas the conditions for authorization of long-term storage contracts specified in Article 32 (4) of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 are therefore met; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1997/98. veiniaastaks koostatud eelkalkulatsioon n&auml;itab, et veiniaasta algul k&auml;ttesaadavad lauaveinikogused &uuml;letavad rohkem kui nelja kuu varu v&otilde;rra k&otilde;nealuse aasta tavap&auml;rase tarbimise; m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artikli 32 l&otilde;ikes 4 kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud pikaajaliste ladustuslepingute s&otilde;lmimise lubamise tingimused on seep&auml;rast t&auml;idetud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the abovementioned forward estimate indicates the existence of surpluses of all types of table wine and of table wines which stand in close economic relationship to those types of table wine; whereas it is necessary by the same token to open this possibility for grape must, concentrated grape must and rectified concentrated grape must; </inglise>
<eesti> eespool nimetatud eelkalkulatsioon n&auml;itab igat t&uuml;&uuml;pi lauaveinide ja nendega majanduslikult tihedalt seotud lauaveinide &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;ki; on vaja s&auml;testada v&otilde;imalus s&otilde;lmida k&otilde;nealuste lauaveinit&uuml;&uuml;pide puhul pikaajalisi lepinguid; selline v&otilde;imalus peaks olema lisaks ka viinamarjavirde, kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde ja puhastatud kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the market for must and concentrated must for grape juice production is expanding and to promote uses of vine products other than winemaking permission should be granted for must and concentrated grape must placed under a storage contract covered by Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1059/83 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1262/96 (4), that is intended for grape juice production to be sold from the fifth month of the contract onwards on simple notification by the producer to the intervention agency; whereas to promote export of these products this same possibility should apply; </inglise>
<eesti> viinamarjamahla valmistamiseks m&otilde;eldud viinamarjavirde ja kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde turg areneb, ning et soodustada viinamarjatoodete kasutamist muul otstarbel kui veinivalmistamine, tuleks lubada komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1059/83, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1262/96, osutatud ladustuslepinguga h&otilde;lmatud viinamarjavirde ja kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde m&uuml;&uuml;mist, mis on m&otilde;eldud viinamarjamahla valmistamiseks, alates lepingu kehtimise viiendast kuust tootja poolt sekkumisasutusele lihtkirjaliku teatise alusel; sama v&otilde;imalust tuleks kohaldada, et soodustada nende toodete v&auml;ljavedamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Wine, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las veinituru korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
